defaultWritten submission from The Prince’s Trust (LPG 53)defaultOverview: defaultThe Prince’s Trust helps disadvantaged young people to get their lives on track. It supports 13 to 30 year-olds who are unemployed and those struggling at school and at risk of exclusion. Many of the young people helped by The Trust are in or leaving care, facing issues such as homelessness or mental health problems, or they have been in trouble with the law. 
defaultThe Trust’s programmes give vulnerable young people the practical and financial support needed to stabilise their lives, helping develop self-esteem and skills for work. The Trust supported 55,801 young people between April 2012 and March 2013. 
defaultThe Prince’s Trust Public Sector Team raises funds from
default&#xa0;
defaultgovernment, local authority, lottery and other statutory sources. In England the Public Sector team is made up of 30 people who work in three areas:
default
